wiki.summary: "Don't Let Me Down" is a song by American DJ duo The Chainsmokers. It was released the follow-up single to "Roses" on February 5, 2016, through Disruptor and Columbia Records. The song features vocals from American singer Daya. "Don't Let Me Down" received positive reviews for its production and Daya's vocals, and was a commercial success, becoming The Chainsmoker's second top 10 hit in the United States (and Daya's first). wiki.content: "Don't Let Me Down" is a song by American DJ duo The Chainsmokers. It was released the follow-up single to "Roses" on February 5, 2016, through Disruptor and Columbia Records. The song features vocals from American singer Daya. "Don't Let Me Down" received positive reviews for its production and Daya's vocals, and was a commercial success, becoming The Chainsmoker's second top 10 hit in the United States (and Daya's first). It also reached top 10 positions in Australia, Austria, Canada, Finland, Germany, New Zealand, Norway, Sweden, and Switzerland. Read more on Last.fm.
